</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_Benefits_of_Social_Learning_Understanding_its_Impact_in_Education_and_the_Workplace_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708446927" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_Benefits_of_Social_Learning_Understanding_its_Impact_in_Education_and_the_Workplace_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708446927 1536w" width="1642" height="1094" alt="The Benefits of Social Learning Understanding its Impact in Education and the Workplace - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:1f50a914-3b2b-40e3-8a91-5e0e726e0637" title="The Benefits of Social Learning: Understanding its Impact in Education and the Workplace - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-121_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-122_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by puhimec via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-124_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Before diving deeper into the topic, let's clarify what social learning is. Social learning refers to the process of learning through observation, imitation, and interaction with others. It's a collaborative approach that emphasises the exchange of knowledge, ideas, and experiences among individuals within a community or network.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-126_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-127_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-128_ pf-heading-1-h3">The evolution of learning
